over you.’  Soon afterwards she shut her eyes and died, and was
buried in the garden; and the little girl went every day to her grave
and wept, and was always good and kind to all about her. And the
snow fell and sprea d a beautiful white covering over the grave; but
by the time the spring came, and the sun had melted it away again,
her father had married another wife.","Grimms’ Fairy Tales, by Jacob Grimm and Wilhelm Grimm.pdf"
